void NS::Client::register_gid ( Net::GlobalId &  gid  )  throw (Util::IOError) [virtual]

Register a GlobalId The process call this method to register a global id to the server. If the global id 'gid' is GlobalId::NO_SITE, then the server allocates a new identifier. If the global id 'gid' is not GlobalId::NO_SITE, then the server register the identifier as an valid identifier and return the same value.

Parameters:
gid (IN) a previous global id, if any
gid (OUT) the new generated global id

Implements NS::Interface.
